Linlin, here's what we'll do.

00:11:38.240 --> 00:11:39.240
Let's close our eyes.

00:11:39.879 --> 00:11:40.840
Listen carefully.

00:11:41.360 --> 00:11:42.039
See if you can hear

00:11:42.039 --> 00:11:42.919
the sound of mangrove frogs.

00:11:45.440 --> 00:11:46.240
Dad.

00:11:46.519 --> 00:11:47.639
It stinks here.

00:11:48.159 --> 00:11:49.120
I'm scared.

00:11:49.360 --> 00:11:50.480
I want to go home.

00:11:51.759 --> 00:11:52.240
Okay.

00:11:52.879 --> 00:11:54.480
Another day, I'll catch one and show you.

00:11:59.480 --> 00:12:00.360
See it?

00:12:00.519 --> 00:12:01.519
That's a mangrove frog.

00:12:01.600 --> 00:12:02.919
A mangrove frog, that's a mangrove frog.

00:12:03.159 --> 00:12:04.159
Sketch it, sketch it.

00:12:04.159 --> 00:12:05.320
I'll catch it for you to see.

00:12:07.080 --> 00:12:07.600
Got it.

00:12:11.600 --> 00:12:13.039
It's dead.

00:12:20.399 --> 00:12:20.960
Dad.

00:12:21.200 --> 00:12:23.559
Could this be the last

00:12:23.840 --> 00:12:25.120
mangrove frog here?

00:12:25.840 --> 00:12:26.600
How could that be?

00:12:27.600 --> 00:12:28.799
As long as the mangroves are here,

00:12:29.360 --> 00:12:30.679
there will definitely be mangrove frogs.

00:12:31.720 --> 00:12:32.639
But Grandpa said

00:12:32.960 --> 00:12:33.799
when he was little,

00:12:33.919 --> 00:12:35.320
there were even tigers in Shenzhen.

00:12:35.840 --> 00:12:37.279
They're gone now too, aren't they?